headline: Disappointing Q2 Results and Lower Outlook Might Change the Case for Investing in Eastman Chemical (EMN)
summary: Eastman Chemical recently reported second quarter 2025 earnings that came in below consensus and issued a third quarter outlook that fell short of expectations, citing a challenging global macroeconomic environment and adverse tariff impacts as major headwinds. This development has prompted analysts to cut earnings estimates for the third quarter and full year 2025, highlighting ongoing industry difficulties and bearish sentiment regarding Eastman’s near-term prospects.
